The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Rio not to appeal
London: Manchester United and England defender Rio Ferdinand has dropped plans to continue his fight against an eight-month ban for missing a drugs test. He had the option of taking his case to the Court of Arbitration for Sport in Switzerland, but by doing so he ran the risk of his sentence being increased to a maximum of two years. (reuters)  Copyright 
